Peel and finely chop the @red onion{1}(peeled and finely chopped) and roughly chop the @coriander{3}(roughly chopped). Drain and thoroughly rinse the @organic black beans{1}. Slice the @yellow pepper{1} into thin matchsticks (discard the core). Cut across the matchsticks to create very small cubes of pepper.

Heat @olive oil{1/2%tbsp} in a #nonstick frying pan{} on medium heat. Once hot, add in the @diced chorizo{1}, all but @onion{1%tbsp} of the onion and half the pepper and cook for ~{4%minutes}. Add in the @chopped tomatoes{1} and stir in the @Mexican spice{1/2}. Stir in @?sugar{1/2%tsp} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Guacamole ==

To make the guacamole, slice lengthways into the @avocado{1} until you reach the stone in the middle. Slide the #knife{} around the stone and pull it apart - you should have two neat halves. Remove the stone and scoop out the flesh (scrape the inside of the skin to get that fantastic green colour).

Mash the avocado with a #fork{} until it has a nice, spreadable consistency. Add a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{} with a little squeeze of @lime{1/2} juice. Mix in @coriander{1%tbsp}(chopped). Taste for seasoning and add more lime juice and salt if needed.

== Black Bean Salsa ==

Mix half the black beans into the tomato sauce. Once the tomato sauce has thickened up (about ~{10%minutes}), turn off the heat. Once off the heat, stir in @coriander{1/2%tbsp}(chopped).

> The water in the sauce should have disappeared, leaving a nice, chunky salsa.

Mix the remaining black beans with the remaining chopped pepper. Stir in @coriander{1/2%tbsp}(chopped) and the remaining chopped onion. Squeeze over a bit of lime juice and stir in @olive oil{1%tbsp}. Season with a pinch of salt and pepper.

== Assembly ==

Stick the @corn tortilla{4} in the #oven{} on 100 degrees for a few mins to warm up. Cut the tortillas into quarters. Lay a quarter on each #plate{} and cover with a spoonful of salsa.

Lay on another quarter of the tortilla and spread on a thin layer of guacamole. Keep layering the tortilla, salsa and guacamole. Finally spoon the black bean mixture and any remaining coriander over the top of each stack. Ándale!